Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.44,0:00:08.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's room 901, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.26,0:00:10.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, on the top floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.64,0:00:14.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you snuck into the car, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.13,0:00:17.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.37,0:00:18.80,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.80,0:00:21.25,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,All children should have such energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.25,0:00:22.56,DCMain,WOMAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.56,0:00:23.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.57,0:00:24.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.54,0:00:35.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it's down that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.28,0:00:36.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You always do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.29,0:00:38.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a game, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.65,0:00:40.96,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.62,0:00:53.24,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I-I did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.41,0:01:01.19,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.24,0:01:05.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's Takarada-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.75,0:01:08.56,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it serves him right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.56,0:01:10.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, we should call an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.36,0:01:12.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We're too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.11,0:01:13.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's been two hours
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.42,0:01:16.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,since he was strangled to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.45,0:01:18.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Strangled?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.82,0:01:19.68,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.26,0:01:26.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A canvas stained black with crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.36,0:01:29.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,With brilliant detective \Nskills, its color is changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.91,0:01:32.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The mysterious case of a man murdered twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.43,0:01:34.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody must be lying somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.56,0:01:37.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth with the \Nbody of a child and the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:40.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.97,0:03:25.97,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(396,1)}The Man Who Died Twice \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.78,0:03:23.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,“The Man Who Died Twice, Part One!”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.60,0:03:38.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Takarada Yoichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.53,0:03:41.82,Yoichi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Takarada Yoichi (48) \NMoneylender
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.79,0:03:41.82,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That notoriously unscrupulous moneylender?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:45.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to his secretary \NShinkai Haruyuki-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.09,0:03:50.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Takarada was renting this room \Nso he could write a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.28,0:03:50.20,Haruyuki,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Shinkai Haruyuki (27) \NTakarada's Secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.56,0:03:55.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, I heard he \Nself-published books in his spare time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.29,0:03:56.13,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Doers are Winners\NSwallow It Whole\NPrey
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.80,0:04:00.62,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,And Takarada-san had come to \Nthis room today to write, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:03:57.42,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Prey
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.62,0:04:01.49,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:03.47,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,He'd been in here since \Nthis morning by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.95,0:04:07.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know he was such an evil man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.15,0:04:09.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You'd been hired to come work for him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.63,0:04:14.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we'd never met before, \Nhe suddenly called before noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.43,0:04:18.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He had received a murder threat in the mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.74,0:04:22.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted me to come at three to discuss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.38,0:04:24.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But when I came for our appointment...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.26,0:04:27.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The threat had already been carried out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.34,0:04:30.66,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This seems to be that letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:32.45,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It was on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:38.71,Letter,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}I will kill the monstrous \NTakarada Yoichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:38.71,Letter,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Grudge. \NHatred. \NMurder!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.78,0:04:36.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He's preyed on countless people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.13,0:04:38.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,One of his victims must have sought revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:43.40,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,When the letter arrived at the mansion \Nthis morning, that's what I thought, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.94,0:04:47.56,DCItalic,TAKARADA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to see them try.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.38,0:04:52.85,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to allow
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.74,0:04:56.73,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,his victim to become a killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.08,0:04:58.46,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.14,0:05:00.82,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,while the president was napping...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.60,0:05:02.99,DCItalic,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.88,0:05:07.31,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But I was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.79,0:05:16.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be asking you about the \Ndamage you did to the body later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.21,0:05:18.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, the murder is \Nthe more pressing matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.02,0:05:20.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.05,0:05:24.38,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,He had too many victims who hated him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:28.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But is one of them really the murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.48,0:05:29.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:30.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.88,0:05:32.00,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.92,0:05:35.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Did you figure something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.24,0:05:36.06,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.27,0:05:38.74,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,After knocking the victim unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.74,0:05:41.40,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,by striking him on the back of \Nthe head with a blunt object,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.40,0:05:44.82,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,they strangled him with some \Nkind of rope-like object.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.14,0:05:48.96,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,We believe he died roughly two \Nhours before the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.96,0:05:51.06,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,That would be around 1 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.06,0:05:51.84,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:55.82,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,This is the building administrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.15,0:05:59.17,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He says he saw a suspicious \Nwoman right around that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:00.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.38,0:06:04.96,Kinsaku,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Tomii Kinsaku (58) \NBuilding Administrator
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.53,0:06:05.76,DCMain,TOMII,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}After lunch, I came to this \Nfloor while doing my rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.12,0:06:08.05,DCMain,TOMII,0000,0000,0000,,Just then,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.58,0:06:12.34,DCMain,TOMII,0000,0000,0000,,a blonde I didn't recognize came \Nwalking away from this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.80,0:06:16.86,DCMain,TOMII,0000,0000,0000,,That was around one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.86,0:06:17.43,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:22.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you recognize this woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.32,0:06:27.19,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Her sunglasses are covering her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.48,0:06:31.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not necessarily a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.31,0:06:34.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They could've be trying to look like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.46,0:06:37.44,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Since there's only footage of her leaving,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.98,0:06:39.90,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,she must've snuck in \Nthrough the rear entrance
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.90,0:06:43.75,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,and exited through the front \Nbecause she'd been seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.02,0:06:48.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did the president not lock his door?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.72,0:06:53.30,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it, he had \Na habit of using the chain lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.67,0:06:58.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he was so worried about the \Nletter that he called a detective,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.82,0:07:01.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he wouldn't have let any strange \Npeople into his room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.02,0:07:06.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't forgotten that \Nit could be someone he knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.40,0:07:07.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.63,0:07:10.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,His family have finished \Nidentifying the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.19,0:07:13.72,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,His wife and younger brother, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.72,0:07:14.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go meet them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.20,0:07:21.46,Mika,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Takarada Mika (36) \NTakarada's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.38,0:07:21.46,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}How am I going to go on living by myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.74,0:07:22.92,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.75,0:07:26.21,Koji,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Takarada Koji (42) \NTakarada's Younger Brother
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.92,0:07:26.21,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Who on earth would kill my dear brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:31.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, where were you around \N1 PM this afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.17,0:07:34.79,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,You think I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:39.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is just a formality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.43,0:07:42.22,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course they suspect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.22,0:07:45.19,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be inheriting his fortune \Nand the insurance money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.43,0:07:47.77,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who resented Takarada!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.18,0:07:50.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you around 1 PM?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.00,0:07:55.57,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I was at home organizing the \Nstorehouse like Takarada asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.06,0:07:57.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.20,0:07:59.08,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, Koji-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.40,0:08:02.83,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,I was wandering around Shinjuku.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.15,0:08:06.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Can anyone verify that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.07,0:08:13.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's a no, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:14.74,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.50,0:08:17.64,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,The wife is telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.85,0:08:19.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.16,0:08:22.24,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I was in the study until I left the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.24,0:08:24.15,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,just after 2 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:29.07,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Around 1 PM, she was in the storehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.07,0:08:30.19,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Shinkai...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.44,0:08:33.19,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. I'm so glad to have you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.19,0:08:33.95,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.81,0:08:37.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.25,0:08:38.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So that leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.10,0:08:40.78,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.78,0:08:43.79,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's weird \Nto assume family did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.97,0:08:48.28,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but could we continue \Nthis discussion at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.98,0:08:53.09,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.60,0:08:55.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.75,0:08:56.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll join you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.60,0:08:57.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.16,0:09:01.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi-kun, could you \Ninvestigate the other case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.35,0:09:03.56,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.00,0:09:10.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If only he'd noticed the president was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:14.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't have committed his crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:19.53,Station,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,MPD Beika Station
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.01,0:09:19.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Atoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.84,0:09:20.71,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.02,0:09:24.91,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, I was aware of President \NTakarada's unscrupulous practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.26,0:09:27.43,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But I assumed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.43,0:09:30.56,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,his victims were fools for allowing \Nthemselves to be preyed upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.56,0:09:32.48,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.48,0:09:35.67,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,one of them took their entire family with them
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:37.34,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,and committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:42.40,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Their child wasn't even one year old yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:44.27,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,For the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:48.19,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I blamed myself for helping the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.64,0:09:52.07,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Then this morning, the letter arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.18,0:09:54.64,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought whoever had sent it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.04,0:10:00.39,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,must've been a victim like the \None who killed their own child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:02.13,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.40,0:10:05.64,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't want them to commit a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:12.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But why did you decide to \Nkill Takarada yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.32,0:10:16.11,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,As long as he was around, \Nmore victims would've been born!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.59,0:10:18.33,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I had to kill him myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.77,0:10:24.22,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it would be a way \Nto atone for helping him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.22,0:10:26.17,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But I was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.73,0:10:29.35,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,They had already sullied their own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.63,0:10:33.86,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But the killer isn't necessarily \None of Takarada's victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.49,0:10:38.86,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Detective, do you really think \Nsomeone in his family did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.86,0:10:42.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.46,0:10:46.87,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,I hated my brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.04,0:10:49.66,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.66,0:10:52.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But earlier, Mika-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.64,0:10:55.86,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Koji-san has made a living deceiving people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.86,0:10:58.82,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, after failing \Nin one of his attempts,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.82,0:11:01.78,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,he came crying to Takarada to \Nbail him out of the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:03.57,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,but he refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.57,0:11:05.89,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,He was forced to go into hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.53,0:11:08.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So he resented him for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.42,0:11:12.27,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,But three days ago, he asked \Nus to take him in for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.84,0:11:16.27,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,And today, Takarada was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.67,0:11:18.32,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:20.15,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Is this because I suspected you earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.43,0:11:22.16,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just telling them the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:26.68,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're making it sound like I \Ncame home to kill my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.23,0:11:32.81,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Detective, I just happened to come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.81,0:11:36.76,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,One of his victims must've killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.76,0:11:38.92,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, there are plenty of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.93,0:11:48.56,Kyoko,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Kinoshita Kyoko (40) \NTakarada Family Housekeeper
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.12,0:11:45.26,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.26,0:11:48.56,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It seems it's true that a \Nlot of people hated him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.74,0:11:52.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then he must've received a \Nlot of threatening letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.71,0:11:54.73,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He did, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:56.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.33,0:11:58.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.67,0:12:00.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.50,0:12:05.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Takarada-san received threatening \Nletters all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.87,0:12:10.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,His housekeeper said he was even \Nattacked with a knife once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.96,0:12:13.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But it didn't bother him at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.98,0:12:16.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So why did he decide
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.13,0:12:19.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to ask you about it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.12,0:12:24.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He even laughed it off \Nin front of everyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:28.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,before calling you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.88,0:12:31.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he had a special reason for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.96,0:12:33.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.88,0:12:38.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Takarada knew who was trying to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.45,0:12:42.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he laughed it off so \Nthey would let their guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.36,0:12:45.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then he was going to hire me \Nto investigate and expose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.80,0:12:47.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.05,0:12:47.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.02,0:12:49.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.98,0:12:52.93,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The killer is not only one of his own,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.93,0:12:56.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but also one of the three people \Nwho were there at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.50,0:12:59.21,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But mister, of those three people...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.73,0:13:03.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Since Shinkai-kun stabbed the body
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.58,0:13:05.97,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,without realizing Takarada had \Nalready been strangled, he's out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.31,0:13:09.72,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,And if his wife Mika-san has an alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.18,0:13:11.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then that leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.02,0:13:14.62,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.72,0:13:18.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.58,0:13:19.40,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.06,0:13:20.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.04,0:13:23.31,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.31,0:13:26.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They found fingerprints on the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.29,0:13:30.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yours, Takarada Koji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.24,0:13:33.04,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You must be joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.62,0:13:35.29,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoko-san, come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.51,0:13:38.58,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? Did you call me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.94,0:13:42.76,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Call my lawyer Watari-sensei \Nand have him come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.76,0:13:45.33,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him we need to discuss the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.33,0:13:49.65,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,And tell Beika Health I need \Nto discuss the insurance claim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.65,0:13:50.47,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.47,0:13:52.19,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.07,0:13:54.41,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.41,0:13:58.35,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we know this man \Ndid it, the case is settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.55,0:14:02.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we're not certain it's him yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.95,0:14:07.10,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for this moment to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:08.77,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Now that it's over,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.77,0:14:12.70,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I can finally say I only married \NTakarada for his money.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.08,0:14:17.71,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Since he was such an evil man, I was \Nhoping he would die sooner, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.20,0:14:20.43,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Koji-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.68,0:14:24.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I feel dizzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.18,0:14:26.97,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with this woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.15,0:14:30.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, Koji-san, you \Nsent Takarada-san that letter
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.11,0:14:34.30,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,to make the murder seem like the work
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.30,0:14:36.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,of someone who resented him,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.98,0:14:39.85,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and then killed him to get revenge
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.15,0:14:42.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,for the events of two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.36,0:14:43.88,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.88,0:14:46.07,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't write that letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.37,0:14:48.49,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But your fingerprints are on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.08,0:14:51.41,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:54.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How can he be so composed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.20,0:14:56.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.55,0:14:57.68,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.68,0:15:00.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Let me know if there are any developments.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.97,0:15:02.80,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.11,0:15:05.71,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Is Koji-san the suspect now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.96,0:15:09.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, though he seems to be denying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.20,0:15:14.30,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Detective, he didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.30,0:15:15.60,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,He has an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:16.97,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.33,0:15:20.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,W-W-Wait, wh-what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.12,0:15:30.13,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,When Koji-san came to the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.48,0:15:33.08,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,the president told me to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.46,0:15:38.03,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,he didn't need to be bailed out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:41.78,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,So when Koji-san secretly went out today,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.78,0:15:43.00,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I followed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.84,0:15:48.67,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Koji-san seemed to be waiting \Nfor someone on the roof
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.99,0:15:51.01,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,of an apartment building at \Na hero show for families.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.35,0:15:55.18,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I watched him the whole \Ntime, but no one came.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.51,0:15:59.02,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he had been stood up, so I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.54,0:16:03.27,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,That was between just before 1:00 and 1:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.52,0:16:08.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But you said you were at the mansion then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:11.46,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,Because the police suspected his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.72,0:16:15.37,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I lied in order to protect her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.37,0:16:17.66,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What? You lied?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.11,0:16:22.30,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,But now that Koji-san is being accused,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.30,0:16:24.17,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I have to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.62,0:16:29.14,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,The housekeeper should be able to \Nverify the wife's story, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.46,0:16:31.30,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.54,0:16:33.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.16,0:16:37.85,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, we were able to verify his story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.16,0:16:41.18,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,The rooftop must've been \Ncrowded with families, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.61,0:16:42.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.22,0:16:47.81,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,So that secretary was following me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.60,0:16:52.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So he was so composed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.41,0:16:55.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,because he knew he was being followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.82,0:16:59.58,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinkai-san was actually able \Nto verify Koji-san's alibi,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.58,0:17:02.50,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and not Mika-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.81,0:17:05.18,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,The tables have turned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.18,0:17:07.60,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Now I have someone to back up my alibi,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.60,0:17:10.19,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,and you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.19,0:17:11.58,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Not a single one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.88,0:17:12.88,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.32,0:17:14.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Kinoshita-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.48,0:17:18.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,you were out at the hospital all afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.53,0:17:19.56,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.35,0:17:22.52,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.04,0:17:24.19,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.19,0:17:26.64,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need someone to back up my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.05,0:17:28.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.38,0:17:30.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if Koji-san didn't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.92,0:17:34.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,then why are his fingerprints on the letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.37,0:17:36.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.50,0:17:40.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They used a piece of paper that \Nhad his fingerprints on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.13,0:17:43.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So the real killer could make \Nit look like he'd done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.48,0:17:45.79,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea who you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.96,0:17:49.21,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Killing my brother wouldn't \Nbenefit me in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.44,0:17:52.76,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,But you'd finally get his fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.76,0:17:56.38,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but I wouldn't go through \Nthe trouble of killing him for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.22,0:18:01.93,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.18,0:18:03.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.81,0:18:05.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What did he tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.28,0:18:09.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.33,0:18:12.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.66,0:18:16.32,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Takarada had terminal cancer \Nand only six months to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.75,0:18:18.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.39,0:18:20.18,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I just needed to wait six months
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.49,0:18:23.61,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,before I'd get his fortune \Nand insurance money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.61,0:18:28.08,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of idiot would do something \Nstupid to risk losing it all?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.84,0:18:35.26,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This must be her last card, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.76,0:18:41.89,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.68,0:18:45.98,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.33,0:18:52.27,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,So after you came back \Nfrom relieving yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.50,0:18:55.62,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,and this wig and these sunglasses were here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.62,0:18:56.60,DCMain,HOMELESS,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.60,0:19:00.41,DCMain,HOMELESS,0000,0000,0000,,It was stuffed into my things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.88,0:19:03.32,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they thought it was \Na garbage collection site,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.32,0:19:04.81,DCMain,POLICE B,0000,0000,0000,,and were trying to dispose of their disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.81,0:19:06.88,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.88,0:19:09.91,DCMain,POLICE A,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but we'd like to borrow this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.20,0:19:13.19,DCMain,HOMELESS,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, just give them back later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.51,0:19:19.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Takarada Mika-san, the \Nhair sample you gave us
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.75,0:19:24.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,matched the hair we took \Nfrom the wig that was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.92,0:19:25.47,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.72,0:19:28.14,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.14,0:19:30.48,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about that wig.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.92,0:19:34.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There must've been some reason \Nyou couldn't wait six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.88,0:19:39.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but that wig had \Nbeen thrown away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.82,0:19:41.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are much more certain\Nways of getting rid of something,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.40,0:19:42.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,if that's what they wanted to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.64,0:19:43.69,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.31,0:19:47.66,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,You've been waiting for your chance \Nto kill my brother, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.88,0:19:51.34,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,And then a convenient scapegoat
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.34,0:19:54.29,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,like me showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.58,0:19:55.94,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that was scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.94,0:19:58.65,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,You almost got away with framing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.24,0:20:06.71,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,I was here at home when Takarada was killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.71,0:20:08.56,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,You have to believe me, Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.78,0:20:11.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Let's talk at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.83,0:20:13.06,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Please come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.49,0:20:16.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That settles that. Let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.56,0:20:18.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But, mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.11,0:20:20.55,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I need to use the bathroom first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.94,0:20:24.18,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.18,0:20:26.17,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.10,0:20:31.40,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The woman who had remained married \Nto Takarada for his money
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.75,0:20:35.92,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,planned to murder her husband when Koji-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.92,0:20:37.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the perfect scapegoat, showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.60,0:20:42.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Using a sheet of paper with \NKoji-san's fingerprints on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.94,0:20:44.56,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,she wrote and sent a threatening letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.56,0:20:47.60,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then she visited the rented \Nroom and strangled Takarada.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.11,0:20:51.64,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She fled while wearing \Nthe disguise she prepared
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.64,0:20:54.02,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,in case anyone saw her and \Ndisposed of it when she was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.96,0:20:59.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That should be the story, but \Nit all seems too careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.03,0:21:00.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.69,0:21:02.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Koji-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.69,0:21:06.82,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're the only one I \Ncan ask about legal stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.07,0:21:11.40,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,If a wife murders her husband, she \Ncan't inherit his fortune, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.40,0:21:13.76,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, the money would...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.50,0:21:15.67,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.67,0:21:18.71,DCMain,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,The head of the household \Nonly has one younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.06,0:21:20.93,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.45,0:21:24.84,DCItalic,KOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Killing my brother wouldn't \Nbenefit me in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.13,0:21:28.54,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if he sets up his brother's \Nwife and his killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.54,0:21:30.52,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he can keep all the money to himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.91,0:21:31.85,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.85,0:21:33.60,Kyoko2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Kyoko
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.85,0:21:33.60,Hospital,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Afternoon Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.93,0:21:38.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So Koji-san knew you were \Ngoing to the hospital today?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.22,0:21:39.10,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.10,0:21:42.67,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Not just Koji-san, but everyone knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.67,0:21:44.65,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to inconvenience anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.65,0:21:47.36,DCMain,KYOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so I wrote my appointment on the calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.67,0:21:49.58,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So he knew
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.95,0:21:52.93,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,that she wouldn't have anyone \Nto verify her alibi today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.89,0:21:54.77,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.77,0:21:56.12,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.12,0:21:57.52,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,This is your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.52,0:22:01.17,DCMain,MIKA,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd just kept up the lie \Nand backed up my story!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.88,0:22:03.25,DCMain,SHINKAI,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.60,0:22:06.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What a disgusting woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.75,0:22:09.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She won't get off that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.53,0:22:13.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he tricked the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.06,0:22:15.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, all of us, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.73,0:22:23.48,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let him get what he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.36,0:23:49.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If they killed Takarada and made \Nit look like his wife did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.78,0:23:52.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's what they were doing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.28,0:23:55.78,DCMain,TOMII,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san truly is a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.10,0:23:59.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We made a mistake from the very start.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.26,0:24:02.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We assumed someone in his family did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.42,0:24:04.83,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But, Mori-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.00,0:24:07.59,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't prove they killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Man Who Died Twice \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.62,0:24:13.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is “The \NMan Who Died Twice, Part Two!”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Calendar
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.50,0:24:32.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.80,0:24:34.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A calendar!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.14,0:24:36.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The killer is a mystery, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.77,0:24:37.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.12,0:24:38.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Two death!
